There are several tricks in a prepared gardeners tool box to deal with weeds, but foremost is determination to pull them out. The goal here is simply to uproot the weed so that it can't grow back. Other techniques that can help with weeding include mulching to block weeds from the sun, cover crops like barley and clover, and minimizing the disruption of your soil.

